name: Angie Kang
bio:
Creating cookies for fun! I’m a mom of 3 boys, a teacher, and a cookie artist. 
 **No longer going to be taking custom orders**
📍Gaithersburg, MD

It’s been a minute, but I’m still here! ❤️I am working on hopefully getting some new content out soon but in the meantime, I am going to throw it back to my favorite Valentine’s cookie from several years ago that I keep coming back to.

Celebrated my nephew’s first birthday this weekend with a big party!! In Korean tradition, we have the child choose an item to predict their future lol and looks like we will have a future musician in the family 😁 In Korean, the words on the top right “Chut Dol” means first birthday and the bottom left corner is his Korean name. Happy birthday little guy! @conni.kang

When Covid hit, so many plans were derailed. A few years ago, @soencookiegram and I hosted the #wheretonextbakes collab and asked cookiers to tell us where they would love to travel once places opened up again. One of my dream vacations was visiting the beautiful Amalfi Coast! Well I just got back from an amazing trip to Rome and the Amalfi Coast and it really was a dream come true! 

Anyone else make their travel dreams a reality? I’d love to hear where you went!!
Sometimes simple greenery is just enough 😊 Happy Friday!

Happy National Sugar Cookie Day!!!

Christmas is 9 days away and I’ve got a lot of things on my mind, but one of the most important things I want to remind everyone is to spend time with your loved ones around you because that time is so much more precious than any physical gift. ❤️

Reposting some of my favorite Christmas cookies from the past. I simply adored making these cute bears and deer clip art I bought from @tinyselena_ on @etsy to make some fun Christmas cards and they ended up also being perfect for these cookies.

These guys make me hopeful for the time I get to spend with my family and friends. 

What holiday activity are you most looking forward to? 
•
•
•
•
•
• Oval cutter from @brightoncutters
Let it snow! This is still one of my favorite holiday cutters from @kaleidacuts so I’m reposting this tutorial for all my snow lovers!

It’s almost time!! I still have lots of presents to wrap, but looking forward to spending lots of family time this week! 

This cookie from a few years back is inspired by a @minted Christmas card!

Just relaxing today and spending time baking. These chocolate chip coconut cookies are hitting the spot. Even if you’re not a coconut fan, the flakes just give a little bit of depth to the cookie and it’s sooo yummy!
Happy New Year everyone!!! I hope 2024 brings wonderful hopes and memories to you all!
